# Appendices

## Appendix A — Core interface contracts (v0.1)

> These are specification-level signatures expressed in Rust-like pseudocode to fix the *shape* of each contract. Exact types are settled during the test-first cycle; what matters here is the surface each test must pin down. All fallible operations return `Result<T, TypedError>` — no panics across interface boundaries.

### A.1 LLM Provider

```rust
/// The cost-model schema lives in core so all callers and the future
/// ML tuner read usage uniformly, regardless of provider.
struct Usage {
    input_tokens:  u64,
    output_tokens: u64,
    cost:          Option<Money>,   // null when provider gives no pricing
}

struct GenerationRequest {
    messages:        Vec<Message>,
    max_output_tokens: u32,         // the output budget; must be respected
    model:           ModelId,
}

struct GenerationResponse {
    content: Vec<ContentBlock>,
    usage:   Usage,
}

trait LlmProvider {              // implemented by plugins; one in v0.1
    fn generate(&self, req: GenerationRequest)
        -> Result<GenerationResponse, ProviderError>;
    fn models(&self) -> Vec<ModelDescriptor>;   // includes cost-model where known
}

enum ProviderError { RateLimited, Unauthorized, BudgetExceeded,
                     Transport(String), Provider(String) }
```

### A.2 Kanban State Machine

```rust
enum TaskState { Backlog, Todo, Ready, Running, Blocked, Done, Archived }

struct Task {
    id:           TaskId,
    state:        TaskState,
    actor:        Option<ActorId>,   // human or agent identity
    depends_on:   Vec<TaskId>,
    block_reason: Option<BlockReason>,
    history:      Vec<StateChange>,  // append-only audit trail
}

struct StateChange { from: TaskState, to: TaskState,
                     actor: ActorId, at: Timestamp, reason: Option<String> }

trait KanbanBoard {              // contract in core; SQLite impl is the v0.1 plugin
    fn create(&self, task: NewTask) -> Result<TaskId, KanbanError>;
    fn transition(&self, id: TaskId, to: TaskState, actor: ActorId,
                  reason: Option<String>) -> Result<(), KanbanError>;
    fn claim(&self, id: TaskId, worker: ActorId) -> Result<(), KanbanError>; // atomic
    fn get(&self, id: TaskId) -> Result<Task, KanbanError>;
}

enum KanbanError { IllegalTransition { from: TaskState, to: TaskState },
                   DependenciesNotDone, AlreadyClaimed,
                   BlockReasonRequired, NotFound }
```

### A.3 Plugin Manifest & Loader

```rust
enum PluginClass { Safe, Unsafe }

enum Capability { FileRead(PathScope), FileWrite(PathScope),
                  Network(HostScope), Shell, Git, /* extensible */ }

struct PluginManifest {
    name:          String,
    version:       SemVer,
    class:         PluginClass,
    capabilities:  Vec<Capability>,        // must be empty for Safe plugins
    implements:    Vec<(ContractId, SemVer)>,
}

trait PluginLoader {             // core, non-negotiable
    fn discover(&self) -> Vec<PluginManifest>;
    fn load(&self, m: &PluginManifest) -> Result<LoadedPlugin, LoadError>;
    // load() MUST consult SecurityModule::verify before instantiation
}

enum LoadError { ManifestInvalid, IncompatibleContractVersion,
                 SecurityRejected(String), SafePluginRequestedCapability }
```

### A.4 Security Module

```rust
trait SecurityModule {           // core; the root of trust; never a plugin
    fn self_check(&self) -> Result<(), SecurityError>;        // runs first
    fn verify(&self, m: &PluginManifest) -> Result<(), SecurityError>;
    fn stamp(&self, msg: &Message) -> Stamp;                  // issue on a form
    fn invalidate(&self, stamp: Stamp);                       // on transform
    fn audit(&self, decision: SecurityDecision);              // append-only
}

enum SecurityError { IntegrityFailure, CapabilityDenied(Capability),
                     SafePluginViolation }
```

### A.5 Sandbox

```rust
trait SandboxRuntime {           // contract in core; wasmtime impl is core-controlled plugin
    fn execute(&self, code: SafeModule, input: Bytes, limits: ResourceLimits)
        -> Result<Bytes, SandboxError>;
}

struct ResourceLimits { max_memory_bytes: u64, max_wallclock_ms: u64 }

enum SandboxError { MemoryExceeded, Timeout,
                    HostAccessAttempted(Capability), Trap(String) }
```

### A.6 Call Logger

```rust
struct CallLog {
    task:    TaskId,    profile: ProfileId,
    provider: String,   model:  ModelId,
    usage:   Usage,     outcome: CallOutcome,    at: Timestamp,
}
enum CallOutcome { Completed, Failed(String), Partial(String) }

trait CallLogger {               // interface in core; impl is a plugin
    fn record(&self, entry: CallLog) -> Result<(), LogError>;
}
```

### A.7 Human Escalation

```rust
struct Escalation {
    task:    TaskId,
    prompt:  String,
    options: Vec<ActionOption>,   // suggested actions, shown as buttons in Phase 2 UI
}                                 // free-text and stop are ALWAYS implicitly available

enum HumanResponse { Chose(ActionOptionId), FreeText(String), Stop }

